GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
H 1
HOUSE BILL 891
Short Title: Civil Actions/State Agency and AG Litigation. (Public)
Sponsors: Representatives Blackwell, Schietzelt, Blust, and Howard (Primary Sponsors).
For a complete list of sponsors, refer to the North Carolina General Assembly web site.
Referred to: Judiciary 1, if favorable, Rules, Calendar, and Operations of the House
April 14, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT ENACTING THE GOVERNMENT AGENCY FORUM SELECTION ACT AND
3 RELATING TO LITIGATION BY THE ATTORNEY GENERAL.
4 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
5 SECTION 1. Chapter 1 of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new Article
6 to read:
7 "Article 54.
8 "Government Agency Forum Selection Act.
9 "§ 1-665. Government agency forum selection; requirements.
10 (a) It is the public policy of the State of North Carolina that its General Court of Justice
11 maintain primary jurisdiction to hear civil actions involving the State or a local political
12 subdivision of the State, as follows:
13 (1) For matters where a State court has concurrent jurisdiction with a federal
14 court, an action brought by the State or a local political subdivision of the State
15 shall be brought in State court.
16 (2) A State or local political subdivision of the State may file a civil action in
17 federal court rather than State court if the federal court has exclusive
18 jurisdiction over the subject matter of the action.
19 (3) In any case where the State or a local political subdivision of the State is a
20 defendant in a civil action, the State or local political subdivision of the State
21 shall not seek to remove, or consent to removal of, the action from State court
22 to federal court.
23 (b) This Article does not apply to agents of the State acting under G.S. 1-72.2 or
24 G.S. 120-32.6.
25 "§ 1-666. Severability.
26 If any provision of this Article or its application is held invalid or unconstitutional by any
27 court of competent jurisdiction, the invalidity or unconstitutionality shall not affect other
28 provisions or applications of this Article that can be given effect without the invalid or
29 unconstitutional provision or application. Therefore, the provisions of this Article are declared
30 to be severable."
31 SECTION 2. G.S. 114-2.8, as enacted by Section 3D.1 of S.L. 2024-57, reads as
32 rewritten:
33 "§ 114-2.8. Limitation on participation in foreign litigation.litigation.
34 The Attorney General shall initiate actions on behalf of the State to enforce or defend State
35 law and shall not, as a party, amicus, or any other participant in an action pending before a state
*H891-v-1*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 or federal court in another state, any jurisdiction, advance any argument that would result in the
2 invalidation of any statute enacted by the General Assembly."
3 SECTION 3. This act is effective when it becomes law.
